    "objective": "To provide a PK model that combines CBZ and CBZE and incorporates inter- and intra-variability.",
    "covariates": "Tested: Included: Dose, WT, VPA, PHT, PHB on CL of CBZ Dose, WT, VPA, PHT on CL of CBZE",
    "observations": "Ka CBZ fixed to lit values. Vd/F of CBZ and CBZE fixed to literature values. Clearance of CBZ used as input for 1 compartment model of CBZE. Much variability explained by covariate model, allowing for more individualised dosing. The IIV on CBZE CL is very large, which does not allow for dose optimization regarding CBZE exposure, but does allow this for CBZ, due to large portion of variability explained.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "2 * 1 compartment, linear absorption and elimination separately done for CBZ and CBZE",
    "equations": "[CBZ] CL/F=theta1*(Dose**theta2)*(WT**theta3) *(theta4**VPA) *(theta5**PHT) *(theta6**PHB)*exp(eta1) Vd/F=theta7*exp(eta2) Ka=theta8 Cobs=Cipred*(1+eps1)+eps2 [CBZE] CL/F=theta1*(Dose**theta2)*(WT**theta3) *(theta4**VPA) *(theta5**PHT)+eta1 Vd/F=theta6 Ka was set to individuals’ elimination rates of CBZ (CL/Vd), with transformation ratio of 0.65, i.e. 65% of CBZ in blood is eventually converted to CBZE Cobs=Cipred*(1+eps1) VPA=comedication with valproic acid >18 mg/kg/day (yes =1, no=0) PHT=comedication with phenytoin (yes =1, no=0) PHB=comedication with phenobarbital (yes =1, no=0)",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=0.141 theta2=0.406 theta3=0.117 theta4=1.23 theta5=1.44 [CBZ] theta6=1.26 theta7=72 theta8=1.2 omega1=0.0106 omega2=0.184 sigma1=0.0209 sigma2=0.454 [CBZE] theta6=175 omega1=22.6 sigma1=0.0875",
